/PGMAòARIV/XX132/XX/PR

/KAADON OLAM / CROWN OF ALL TIME/PR

/ITThis translation can be sung to the same melody as the Hebrew./PR

/PR

Crown of all time, the one who reigned/PR

before all mortal shape was made,/PR

and when Godòs will brought forth all things/PR

then was the name supreme proclaimed./PR

/PR

And after everything is gone,/PR

yet One alone, awesome, will reign./PR

God was, and is, and will remain,/PR

in splendid balance, over all./PR

/PR

And God is One, no second is,/PR

none can compare, or share Godòs place./PR

Without beginning, without end,/PR

Godòs is all might and royal grace./PR

/PR

This is my God, my help who lives,/PR

refuge from pain in time of trial,/PR

my banner, and my place to fly,/PR

my cupòs portion when, dry, I cry./PR

/PR

To Godòs kind hand I pledge my soul/PR

each time I sleep, again to wake,/PR

